<Heading Size="HeadingSize.Is3">
    Extended Color Variants
</Heading>

<Paragraph>
    Blazorise enumerations such as <Code>Extended Enumeration Variants</Code> and <Code>TextColor</Code> now support <Strong>nested variants</Strong>, enabling more expressive and fine-grained styling options. Previously, only base values like <Code>Background.Success</Code> or <Code>TextColor.Danger</Code> were available; now you can specify variants such as <Code>Background.Success.Subtle</Code> or <Code>TextColor.Success.Emphasis</Code> to match newer design systems and theme palettes.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
    This enhancement is powered by the new <Code>IEnumerationNameBuilder</Code> infrastructure, which allows each CSS provider to define how enumeration names are formatted. For example, the Bootstrap provider can automatically generate class names like <Code>bg-success-subtle</Code> or <Code>text-success-emphasis</Code>. The feature is fully backward-compatible with existing markup and ready for use in all supported frameworks.
</Paragraph>

<Heading Size="HeadingSize.Is3">
    FluentUI Theme Generator
</Heading>

<Paragraph>
    For the first time, Blazorise now includes a built-in theme generator for FluentUI. This allows developers to easily create and customize themes that align with Microsoft's Fluent Design System, enhancing the visual consistency of applications built with Blazorise.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
    We tried to keep the theme as close to the original FluentUI design as possible, while also allowing for customization to fit your application's needs. The theme generator provides a straightforward way to apply FluentUI styles across all Blazorise components, ensuring a cohesive look and feel.
</Paragraph>